# UX/UI Design Principles

> **Framework-agnostic**: This rule contains universal UX/UI principles applicable to any web framework. Framework-specific implementations should be created separately.

## üìã Overview

This rule defines core principles and best practices for creating modern, user-centric web interfaces. Focus on usability, accessibility, visual hierarchy, and responsive design to deliver exceptional user experiences across all devices.

## üéØ Core UX/UI Principles

### 1. User-Centric Design
- **Prioritize user needs**: Design decisions should be based on user research and feedback
- **Reduce cognitive load**: Simplify interfaces, minimize choices, use familiar patterns
- **Progressive disclosure**: Show only essential information first, reveal details on demand
- **Consistency**: Maintain consistent patterns, terminology, and visual language throughout

### 2. Visual Hierarchy
- **Guide attention**: Use size, color, contrast, and spacing to direct user focus
- **F-pattern and Z-pattern**: Structure content to match natural reading patterns
- **Grouping**: Use proximity and visual similarity to group related elements
- **Emphasis**: Highlight primary actions with prominent visual treatment

### 3. Responsive Design
- **Mobile-first approach**: Design for smallest screens first, enhance for larger devices
- **Fluid layouts**: Use flexible grids (CSS Grid, Flexbox) that adapt to screen sizes
- **Content prioritization**: Show critical content first on mobile devices
- **Touch-friendly**: Ensure tap targets are at least 44√ó44px (iOS) or 48√ó48dp (Android)

### 4. Performance & Perception
- **Fast load times**: Optimize assets, lazy load images, minimize bundle sizes
- **Perceived performance**: Use loading states, skeleton screens, optimistic UI updates
- **Smooth interactions**: Maintain 60fps animations, use hardware acceleration
- **Instant feedback**: Provide immediate visual response to user actions

### 5. Accessibility & Inclusivity
- **Semantic HTML**: Use proper HTML elements for better screen reader support
- **Keyboard navigation**: All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- **Color contrast**: Maintain minimum 4.5:1 ratio for normal text (WCAG AA). Prefer designing toward WCAG 2.2 AA (or higher) where feasible.
- **Alternative text**: Provide descriptive alt text for all meaningful images

## ‚úÖ DO (Recommended Practices)

### Layout & Spacing
- ‚úÖ **Use consistent spacing system**: Implement 4px or 8px base grid
- ‚úÖ **Generous whitespace**: Allow content to breathe, prevent visual clutter
- ‚úÖ **Logical grouping**: Group related items together with consistent spacing
- ‚úÖ **Flexible containers**: Use relative units (%, rem, em) over fixed pixels

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Consistent spacing system */
:root {
  --spacing-4: 1rem;
  --spacing-6: 1.5rem;
}
```

### Typography
- ‚úÖ **Type scale**: Use consistent font size progression (e.g., 1.2 or 1.25 ratio)
- ‚úÖ **Line height**: Set 1.4-1.6 for body text, 1.2-1.3 for headings
- ‚úÖ **Line length**: Keep 50-75 characters per line for optimal readability
- ‚úÖ **Font weights**: Use 2-3 font weights maximum (e.g., 400, 600, 700)

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Type scale with consistent ratios */
:root {
  --font-size-base: 1rem;
  --font-size-lg: 1.25rem;
  --font-size-xl: 1.5rem;
  --line-height-normal: 1.5;
}
```

> **Reference**: See [Typography](visual/typography.mdc) for detailed type scale and typography guidelines.

### Colors & Contrast
- ‚úÖ **Limited palette**: Use 3-5 primary colors maximum
- ‚úÖ **Semantic colors**: Define colors for success, warning, error, info states
- ‚úÖ **Contrast ratios**: Test all text/background combinations with tools
- ‚úÖ **Color blindness**: Don't rely on color alone to convey information

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Semantic color system */
:root {
  --color-primary: #0066cc;
  --color-success: #10b981;
  --color-error: #ef4444;
  --color-text-primary: #1f2937;
  --color-text-secondary: #6b7280;
}
```

> **Reference**: See [Colors and Contrast](visual/colors-contrast.mdc) for detailed color system and contrast guidelines.

### Interactive Elements
- ‚úÖ **Clear affordances**: Make clickable elements obviously interactive
- ‚úÖ **Hover/focus states**: Provide clear visual feedback on interaction
- ‚úÖ **Disabled states**: Visually distinguish disabled elements (reduce opacity)
- ‚úÖ **Loading states**: Show loading indicators for async operations

```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Button states -->
<button disabled aria-disabled="true">Submit</button>
<button aria-busy="true">Loading...</button>
```

### Forms & Validation
- ‚úÖ **Clear labels**: Always label form inputs explicitly
- ‚úÖ **Inline validation**: Validate as user types, show immediate feedback
- ‚úÖ **Error messages**: Be specific about what went wrong and how to fix
- ‚úÖ **Autocomplete**: Use appropriate autocomplete attributes

```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Accessible form -->
<label for="email">Email Address</label>
<input 
  type="email" 
  id="email" 
  name="email"
  required
  aria-describedby="email-error">
<span id="email-error" role="alert"></span>
```

> **Reference**: See [Forms and Validation](technical/forms-validation.mdc) for detailed form design patterns.

### Navigation
- ‚úÖ **Clear hierarchy**: Use proper heading levels (h1-h6) in order
- ‚úÖ **Breadcrumbs**: Show current location in deep navigation structures
- ‚úÖ **Active states**: Highlight current page/section in navigation
- ‚úÖ **Skip links**: Provide "skip to main content" for keyboard users

```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Semantic navigation -->
<nav aria-label="Main navigation">
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/" aria-current="page">Home</a></li>
    <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>
<a href="#main-content">Skip to main content</a>
```

> **Reference**: See [Navigation](layout/navigation.mdc) for detailed navigation patterns. See [HTML Best Practices](../../html/html.mdc) for semantic HTML structure.

### Micro-interactions
- ‚úÖ **Subtle animations**: Use transitions to guide attention (200-300ms)
- ‚úÖ **Purposeful motion**: Every animation should serve a purpose
- ‚úÖ **Respect preferences**: Honor `prefers-reduced-motion` media query
- ‚úÖ **Feedback loops**: Confirm user actions with visual feedback

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Respect motion preferences */
.button {
  transition: background-color 200ms;
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .button {
    transition: none;
  }
}
```

## ‚ùå DON'T (Anti-patterns)

### Layout Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Fixed widths**: Don't use fixed pixel widths for containers
- ‚ùå **Inconsistent spacing**: Don't use random spacing values
- ‚ùå **Overcrowding**: Don't pack too much content in limited space
- ‚ùå **Horizontal scrolling**: Avoid horizontal scroll on mobile (except carousels)

```css
/* ‚ùå Bad: Fixed width */
.container { width: 1200px; }

/* ‚úÖ Good: Flexible */
.container { max-width: 1200px; width: 100%; }
```

> **Reference**: See [Responsive Design](layout/responsive-design.mdc) for detailed responsive layout guidelines.

### Typography Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Too many fonts**: Don't use more than 2-3 font families
- ‚ùå **Small text**: Don't use font sizes below 14px for body text
- ‚ùå **Poor line height**: Don't use line heights below 1.4 for paragraphs
- ‚ùå **All caps everywhere**: Don't overuse uppercase text (reduces readability)

```css
/* ‚ùå Bad: Too many fonts */
h1 { font-family: 'Font1'; }
h2 { font-family: 'Font2'; }
p { font-family: 'Font3'; }

/* ‚úÖ Good: Consistent system */
:root { --font-primary: 'Inter', sans-serif; }
h1, h2, p { font-family: var(--font-primary); }
```

> **Reference**: See [Typography](visual/typography.mdc) for detailed typography guidelines.

### Color Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Low contrast**: Don't use light gray text on white backgrounds
- ‚ùå **Too many colors**: Don't create rainbow interfaces
- ‚ùå **Color-only indicators**: Don't rely solely on color for information
- ‚ùå **Bright backgrounds**: Avoid bright colored backgrounds with text

```css
/* ‚ùå Bad: Insufficient contrast */
.text { color: #999999; background: #ffffff; }

/* ‚úÖ Good: Sufficient contrast */
.text { color: #666666; background: #ffffff; }
```

> **Reference**: See [Colors and Contrast](visual/colors-contrast.mdc) for detailed contrast requirements.

### Interaction Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Small tap targets**: Don't make buttons/links smaller than 44√ó44px
- ‚ùå **No feedback**: Don't leave users wondering if their action worked
- ‚ùå **Hidden interactions**: Don't rely on hover-only interactions on touch devices
- ‚ùå **Auto-playing media**: Don't auto-play videos/audio without user consent

```css
/* ‚ùå Bad: Too small */
.button { padding: 4px 8px; }

/* ‚úÖ Good: Touch-friendly */
.button { min-height: 44px; padding: 12px 24px; }
```

### Form Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Placeholder-only labels**: Don't use placeholders as labels
- ‚ùå **Unclear errors**: Don't show generic "Error occurred" messages
- ‚ùå **Reset buttons**: Don't include reset/clear buttons (high risk, low value)
- ‚ùå **CAPTCHA overuse**: Don't use CAPTCHA unless absolutely necessary

```html
<!-- ‚ùå Bad: Placeholder as label -->
<input type="text" placeholder="Enter your name">

<!-- ‚úÖ Good: Proper label -->
<label for="name">Name</label>
<input type="text" id="name" placeholder="e.g., John Smith">
```

> **Reference**: See [Forms and Validation](technical/forms-validation.mdc) for detailed form design patterns.

### Performance Mistakes
- ‚ùå **Unoptimized images**: Don't use full-resolution images without optimization
- ‚ùå **Heavy animations**: Don't animate expensive properties (width, height)
- ‚ùå **Blocking resources**: Don't block rendering with large JavaScript bundles
- ‚ùå **No loading states**: Don't leave users with blank screens during loading

